a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:7;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:7:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:84;s:5:"title";s:82:"Vendasta Services bundles an AI Chat Receptionist trial with new website projects";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-services-bundles-an-ai-chat-receptionist-trial-with-new/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-services-bundles-an-ai-chat-receptionist-trial-with-new/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1770100464;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1770100461;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:2503:"<p>Vendasta is adding a trial version of its AI Chat Receptionist to new websites delivered through Vendasta Services, beginning February 10, 2026. The trial is included with Website Support+ for new website builds or imports.</p>
<h3>What’s changing</h3>
<p>All new Vendasta Services website projects (builds or imports) will ship with a limited AI Chat Receptionist enabled alongside Website Support+.</p>
<h3>What’s included in the trial (Website Support+)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Lead capture: engages visitors and captures lead info 24/7</li>
<li>Basic setup by Vendasta: code embed, site scraping to train the AI, and widget styling to match brand colors</li>
<li>Messaging allowance: 40 messages/month</li>
</ul>
<p>Vendasta notes the limit won’t be strictly enforced until AI credits launch in mid-2026</p>
<h3>Who it applies to</h3>
<p>Eligible services include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Express Website Build</li>
<li>Templated Website</li>
<li>Website Import & Support</li>
<li>Accelerated Templated Website (planned for later)</li>
</ul>
<p>Existing websites aren’t automatically affected unless they’re moved to Website Support+.</p>
<h3>Relationship to Conversations AI</h3>
<p>Vendasta states this limited AI Chat Receptionist is separate from Conversations AI. If a client needs more usage or channels, the recommended path is upgrading to Conversations AI plans (Standard/Pro/Premium), which Vendasta positions as unlocking higher message limits plus features like SMS and voice.</p>
<h3>How it works operationally</h3>
<ul>
<li>Order a qualifying website build/import via Vendasta Services</li>
<li>The AI Chat Receptionist activates automatically with Website Support+</li>
<li>Access continues while Website Support+ remains active; cancelling support removes the receptionist from the site</li>
</ul>
<h3>FAQ highlights (as provided)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Need more than 40 messages: upgrade to Conversations AI tiers for unlimited/full functionality</li>
<li>Want more customization: partners can customize, or purchase an AI Receptionist Setup via the Marketplace</li>
<li>Cancel Website Support+: the AI Chat Receptionist is removed because it’s tied to the subscription</li>
</ul>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/vendasta-services-trial-of-ai-chat-receptionist-included-with-all-new-websites">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/vendasta-services-trial-of-ai-chat-receptionist-included-with-all-new-websites</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:263:"Vendasta is adding a trial version of its AI Chat Receptionist to new websites delivered through Vendasta Services, beginning February 10, 2026. The trial is included with Website Support+ for new website builds or imports. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:263:"Vendasta is adding a trial version of its AI Chat Receptionist to new websites delivered through Vendasta Services, beginning February 10, 2026. The trial is included with Website Support+ for new website builds or imports. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"vendasta";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/vendasta/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-services-bundles-an-ai-chat-receptionist-trial-with-new/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-services-bundles-an-ai-chat-receptionist-trial-with-new/#comments";}i:1;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:77;s:5:"title";s:71:"Vendasta: US SMS activation may take longer due to A2P approval delays";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-us-sms-activation-may-take-longer-due-to-a2p-approval-d/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-us-sms-activation-may-take-longer-due-to-a2p-approval-d/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1770042925;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1770042811;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1127:"<p>Vendasta reported longer approval times for US A2P SMS registrations, a required step to activate SMS messaging for Conversations AI and Broadly 1.0 in the United States.</p>
<h3>What’s happening</h3>
<p>US A2P approvals are taking longer than usual.</p>
<p>Vendasta estimates approvals may take approximately 8–9 business days.</p>
<p>During approval, registrations may remain Pending, and SMS features remain unavailable until carriers approve the registration.</p>
<h3>What Vendasta is doing</h3>
<p>Vendasta says it updated its submission process to align with stricter carrier requirements.</p>
<p>It also says affected registrations were resubmitted on January 22, 2026.</p>
<p>The company says it’s monitoring approvals and continuing to improve the registration experience.</p>
<h3>What partners/customers can do</h3>
<p>To reduce the chance of delays, Vendasta recommends ensuring submissions include accurate business details and a clearly described messaging use case, including explicit opt-in and opt-out language. If needed, Vendasta Support can guide users through the process.</p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:211:"Vendasta reported longer approval times for US A2P SMS registrations, a required step to activate SMS messaging for Conversations AI and Broadly 1.0 in the United States. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:211:"Vendasta reported longer approval times for US A2P SMS registrations, a required step to activate SMS messaging for Conversations AI and Broadly 1.0 in the United States. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"vendasta";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/vendasta/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-us-sms-activation-may-take-longer-due-to-a2p-approval-d/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-us-sms-activation-may-take-longer-due-to-a2p-approval-d/#comments";}i:2;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:74;s:5:"title";s:73:"Vendasta adds Facebook Stories and Reels publishing to Social Marketing";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-facebook-stories-and-reels-publishing-to-social-ma/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-facebook-stories-and-reels-publishing-to-social-ma/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769868000;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769608311;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1963:"<p>Vendasta updated Social Marketing to support three Facebook content formats—Posts, Stories, and Reels—within one publishing workflow.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Social Marketing now supports publishing to Facebook as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Post</li>
<li>Story</li>
<li>Reel</li>
</ul>
<p>Users can select the publish type and preview each format before scheduling or publishing.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>Previously, Social Marketing supported only Facebook Posts, which meant Stories and Reels required separate tools or manual workflows. Consolidating formats into one workflow reduces context switching and helps teams keep Facebook content consistent across brands and locations.</p>
<h3>How to use it</h3>
<p>Single location</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Social Marketing → Create</li>
<li>Start a Post/Story/Short Video workflow</li>
<li>Select Facebook</li>
<li>Advanced Options → choose publish type</li>
<li>Preview → publish/schedule</li>
</ol>
<p>Multi-location</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Social Marketing → Create → Post</li>
<li>Select locations</li>
<li>Choose Facebook</li>
<li>Add caption + media</li>
<li>Advanced Options → select publish type (Post or Story)</li>
<li>Preview → publish/schedule</li>
</ol>
<p>Multi-location via CSV import</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Social Marketing → Create → Import CSV Workflow</li>
<li>Download the new CSV template</li>
<li>Fill and upload CSV</li>
<li>Select locations + Facebook</li>
<li>Review preview (Story auto-selected if enabled in CSV)</li>
<li>Save and schedule</li>
</ol>
<h3>CSV note</h3>
<p>Vendasta states the previous CSV template is no longer supported and the updated template is required to publish Facebook Stories via CSV.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/post-stories-and-reels-to-facebook-from-social-marketing">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/post-stories-and-reels-to-facebook-from-social-marketing</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:171:"Vendasta updated Social Marketing to support three Facebook content formats—Posts, Stories, and Reels within one publishing workflow. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:171:"Vendasta updated Social Marketing to support three Facebook content formats—Posts, Stories, and Reels within one publishing workflow. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"vendasta";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/vendasta/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-facebook-stories-and-reels-publishing-to-social-ma/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-facebook-stories-and-reels-publishing-to-social-ma/#comments";}i:3;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:72;s:5:"title";s:88:"Vendasta adds AI Optimization (AEO) to Snapshot Report to measure AI-answer visibility";s:4:"href";s:93:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-ai-optimization-aeo-to-snapshot-report-to-measure/";s:13:"href-original";s:93:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-ai-optimization-aeo-to-snapshot-report-to-measure/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769695200;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769607614;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1879:"<p>Vendasta introduced a new AI Optimization (AEO) section inside Snapshot Report to help partners and businesses understand whether they’re being surfaced in AI-generated answers.</p>
<h3>What it does</h3>
<p>The AEO section provides a diagnostic view into:</p>
<ul>
<li>whether a site appears accessible to AI systems/crawlers, and</li>
<li>whether the business is mentioned in AI-style answer experiences (Vendasta cites Google AI Mode and ChatGPT).</li>
</ul>
<h3>What’s included</h3>
<p>Website audit: checks basic access signals (e. g., robots.txt and llm.txt where available).</p>
<p>Visibility audit: tests AI-style discovery across prompts/personas/engines using natural-language questions derived from keyword data; supports translated prompts and can show competitor visibility when applicable.<br />
Vendasta notes results are a standardized approximation because AI answers can change by context and over time.</p>
<h3>Who it’s for</h3>
<ul>
<li>Sales teams qualifying prospects and demonstrating competitive gaps</li>
<li>Businesses trying to understand how AI engines surface brands</li>
<li>Partners offering SEO and AI visibility services</li>
<li>Availability and setup</li>
</ul>
<p>Available for Snapshot Reports created after January 21, 2026.</p>
<p>If you use the default Snapshot Report template, it’s enabled automatically.</p>
<p>If your Snapshot Report is customized: Partner Center → Administration → Customize → Sales → Edit Default Snapshot Template → enable AI Optimization → Save.</p>
<p>If you use Markets, the section must also be enabled at the market level where applicable.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/new-ai-optimization-aeo-section-in-snapshot-report">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/new-ai-optimization-aeo-section-in-snapshot-report</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:217:"Vendasta introduced a new AI Optimization (AEO) section inside Snapshot Report to help partners and businesses understand whether they’re being surfaced in AI-generated answers. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:217:"Vendasta introduced a new AI Optimization (AEO) section inside Snapshot Report to help partners and businesses understand whether they’re being surfaced in AI-generated answers. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"vendasta";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/vendasta/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:98:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-ai-optimization-aeo-to-snapshot-report-to-measure/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:102:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-adds-ai-optimization-aeo-to-snapshot-report-to-measure/#comments";}i:4;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:71;s:5:"title";s:72:"Vendasta Social Marketing now supports YouTube publishing and reporting";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-social-marketing-now-supports-youtube-publishing-and-re/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-social-marketing-now-supports-youtube-publishing-and-re/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1769607213;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1769607210;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1238:"<p>Vendasta expanded Social Marketing with a YouTube API integration, adding YouTube as a managed channel alongside existing social destinations.</p>
<h3>What’s new</h3>
<p>Connect a YouTube channel to Social Marketing (Vendasta notes up to two channels per single location)</p>
<p>Draft, schedule, and publish videos directly from Social Marketing, including video metadata (title, description, etc.)</p>
<p>Manage YouTube posts through Post Composer and Campaign workflows</p>
<p>View basic performance metrics: Views, Likes, Comments, and overall Engagement</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>For teams managing multi-channel content calendars, the integration reduces context-switching by keeping YouTube publishing and light reporting inside the same workflow used for other social posts.</p>
<h3>Where to find it</h3>
<p>Connect: Social Marketing → Settings → Connect Accounts</p>
<p>Publish destinations: Post Composer, Post Campaign Composer</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/available-now-publish-and-manage-youtube-videos-directly-in-social-marketing">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/available-now-publish-and-manage-youtube-videos-directly-in-social-marketing</a></p>
";s:11:"format-info";a:2:{s:14:"links-required";a:0:{}s:18:"resources-detected";a:0:{}}s:7:"summary";s:179:"Vendasta expanded Social Marketing with a YouTube API integration, adding YouTube as a managed channel alongside existing social destinations. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:12:"snippet-text";s:179:"Vendasta expanded Social Marketing with a YouTube API integration, adding YouTube as a managed channel alongside existing social destinations. | Read fresh CRM news at WeekCRM";s:6:"draft?";b:0;s:10:"scheduled?";b:0;s:7:"public?";b:1;s:7:"hidden?";b:0;s:8:"current?";b:0;s:10:"favourite?";b:0;s:6:"images";a:0:{}s:6:"thumbs";a:0:{}s:21:"source-main-image-url";s:0:"";s:9:"og-images";a:0:{}s:16:"og-images-thumbs";a:0:{}s:4:"tags";a:3:{i:0;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:3:"CRM";s:4:"href";s:34:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/crm/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:1;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:15:"product updates";s:4:"href";s:46:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/product-updates/";s:8:"current?";b:0;}i:2;a:4:{s:8:"visible?";b:1;s:4:"name";s:8:"vendasta";s:4:"href";s:39:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/tags/vendasta/";s:8:"current?";b:1;}}s:15:"sharing-buttons";b:0;s:7:"related";b:0;s:9:"read-href";s:99:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-social-marketing-now-supports-youtube-publishing-and-re/read/";s:12:"preview-href";b:0;s:14:"comments-count";i:0;s:19:"comments-count-text";s:9:"0 comment";s:18:"new-comments-count";b:0;s:23:"new-comments-count-text";s:0:"";s:14:"comments-link?";b:1;s:13:"href-comments";s:103:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-social-marketing-now-supports-youtube-publishing-and-re/#comments";}i:5;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:37;s:5:"title";s:84:"Vendasta Unlimited calling bonus for Conversations AI Premium extended to mid-2026";s:4:"href";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-unlimited-calling-bonus-for-conversations-ai-premium-ex/";s:13:"href-original";s:94:"https://weekcrm.com/blog/all/vendasta-unlimited-calling-bonus-for-conversations-ai-premium-ex/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1768397131;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1768397129;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1064:"<p>Conversations AI Premium extended its unlimited calling bonus and now lists it as available until mid-2026. Earlier messaging described the bonus as ending in January 2026.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Unlimited calling bonus: extended → mid-2026.</p>
<p>Overage billing: the product states it will provide advance notice before any overage billing takes effect.</p>
<h3>What didn’t change</h3>
<p>Premium continues to include up to 300 minutes per month of AI voice receptionist usage.</p>
<p>Each call supports up to 10 minutes.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>For teams planning voice-volume usage, the extension keeps the cost model stable for longer, while the “advance notice” commitment reduces surprise overages during the transition back to metered billing.</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/unlimited-calling-bonus-for-conversations-ai-premium-extended-until-mid-2026">https://roadmap.vendasta.com/changelog/unlimited-calling-bonus-for-conversations-ai-premium-extended-until-mid-2026</a></p>
